    "body": "> How can I sync with ethereum mainnet blocks? \r\n\r\nYou should find peers eventually, even if bootnodes are overloaded. But why did you set `--nodiscover` -- that disables discovery of nodes?\r\n\r\nHowever, I do hope you are aware that you are configuring your node to be highly exposed to internet attackers, by combining these flags: \r\n`--allow-insecure-unlock  --http --http.addr 0.0.0.0 --http.port 16812 --http.api admin,eth,net,personal,web3 --ws --ws.addr 0.0.0.0 --ws.port 8546 --ws.api admin,eth,net,personal,web3 --authrpc.port 8545 --authrpc.addr 0.0.0.0`\r\n\r\nYou are exposing all apis to the internet, plus allow `unlock` to be used. \r\n\r\n\r\nWhen using flags, the golden priniple is: use defaults. Don't use any flags at all to start with, and only start adding flags if you know what a flag is doing and that you need it. We do our best to ensure that geth's default options are sane. ",
